            <handDesc>
              <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                <seg type="script">
                  <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                  <date notBefore="1350" notAfter="1450">mid-14th mid-15th century</date>
                  <desc>The handwriting is quite uniform, characterized by right-sloping rounded
                    letters, with broad and thick shapes. It shows ancient features: the letters መ,
                    ወ, with angular loops, ዐ ፀ with a triangular shape, ሎ sometimes with the loop
                    attached to the body of the letter (see e.g. <locus target="#12rb"/>, <locus target="#14rb"/>); the numeral ፪ with the two loops attached (e.g, <locus target="#13rb"/>); the numerals sometimes without the dashes above and below
                    (e.g. <locus target="#14rb"/>); coronis on <locus target="#8r"/> (intercolumn)
                    and on <locus target="#24vb"/>; paragraphs signs and cues (numerals) for
                    rubrication (e.g. <locus target="#8v"/>). </desc>
                  <seg type="rubrication">A few lines, alternating with black lines, on the incipit
                    page of text 1.1 (<locus target="#2r"/>), of text 1.2 (<locus target="#28r"/>)
                    and of miracle 8 in text 1.2 (<locus target="#25r"/>); 1-3 lines (sometimes
                    alternating with black lines) on the incipit of the miracles 2, 3, 4, 6, 7;
                    personal names in the supplication formulas; Ethiopic numerals or their
                    elements; elements of the punctuation signs, paragraphs signs; coronis and/or
                    their elements.</seg>
                </seg>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                <locus target="#1r"/>
                <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>The caption is only partly
                  readable: the saint's name cannot be identified; only few letters of his name are
                  readable. The ink colour looks red.</desc>
                <q xml:lang="gez">ስዕለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ <gap reason="illegible"/>ርማም። <foreign xml:lang="en">Image of saint ?</foreign></q>
              </decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                <locus target="#1v"/>
                <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> Gabra Krǝstos</desc>
                <q n="1" xml:lang="gez">ሥዕለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ብ<gap reason="illegible"/>ሴ፡ እግዚአብ<gap reason="illegible"/><foreign xml:lang="en">Image of Saint Gabra Krǝstos, the man
                    of the Lord.</foreign></q>
                <q n="2" xml:lang="gez">ምስለ፡ ፊቃሩ፡ <foreign xml:lang="en">With his band
                    (belt).</foreign></q>
                <note>The first caption is written (in red ink) in the upper part of the miniature,
                  above the saint's figure, the second one (yellow ink?) at the right side of the
                  saint’s figure. The handwriting is most probably the same as the one of the main
                  text.</note>
              </decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                <locus target="#27v"/>
                <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref></desc>
                <q n="1" xml:lang="gez">ስእለ፡ ቅ<gap reason="illegible"/>ስ፡ <gap reason="illegible"/>ብር<gap reason="illegible"/>፡ <foreign xml:lang="en">Image of saint Gabriel
                    (?)</foreign></q>
                <q n="2" xml:lang="gez">ሥዕለ፡ እግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ <gap reason="illegible"/>ስሌ፡ ፍቁራ፡ ወ<gap reason="illegible"/><foreign xml:lang="en">Image of our Lady Mary, with her
                    belowed...</foreign></q>
                <q n="3" xml:lang="gez">ስእለ፡ ቅ<gap reason="illegible"/> ሚካ<gap reason="illegible"/><foreign xml:lang="en">Image of saint Michael</foreign></q>
                <note>The captions of this miniature (in black ink) are mostly unreadable. The
                  handwriting looks recent; different from the one of the main text. </note>
              </decoNote>
